<%- include('partials/header', { pageTitle: 'About' }) %>
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <header class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">About This Tribute</h2>
      <div class="section-rule"></div>
    </header>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">
      The Capoccia–Miotto Family Reunion Tribute is a permanent digital family archive for a connected Italian-American family
      rooted in <strong>Metro Detroit, Michigan</strong>. It honors reunions held since <strong>1977</strong> and invites every
      generation to keep adding photographs, names, and stories.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">
      The Capoccia siblings — <strong>Tony</strong>, <strong>George</strong>, and <strong>Anna Capoccia Miotto</strong> —
      children of Costanzo Capoccia and Maddalena (Madeline) Cervi Capoccia — form the core of this tribute, together with their
      spouses Fran, Christine, and Amerigo “Mickey” Miotto. Anna’s marriage to Mickey joins the Capoccia and Miotto families
      into one extended reunion community. Both family names are welcomed with equal respect.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1rem">
      <strong>Nothing is invented here.</strong> Verified public framework (relationships, key dates from family obituaries and
      records) anchors the pages; richer memories, Italian roots, recipes, and photographs come only from family contributions.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">
      Use the community board, contribution forms, and family tree to help complete every chapter with care and accuracy.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contribute">Contribute Photos</a>
      <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/our-family-story">Our Family Story</a>
      <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/family-tree">Living Family Tree</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
